[00:27.79]Paw Patrol on the TV glow
[00:31.33]Spidey swings real high
[00:34.86]Bluey laughs, Toy Story rolls
[00:38.39]“Woody, Buzz!”—he locks his eyes
[00:41.93]Say it again, yeah, one more time
[00:45.46]“Woody, Buzz!” till we’re all smiling wide
[00:48.99]He’s a big little man with a heart so strong
[00:52.53]Runs down the hall, falls down, gets up, moves on
[00:56.06]Dancing through life like nothing’s wrong
[00:59.59]Full of love, sent from above
[01:03.13]Yeah, heaven knew just what it was doing
[01:06.66]When it sent us him to love
[01:10.19]He plays all day, don’t slow him down
[01:13.72]Feet don’t quit, he’s always found
[01:17.26]Running, laughing, spinning ‘round
[01:20.79]Trips, tumbles—no tears now
[01:24.32]Back on his feet, he’s gone again
[01:27.86]Braver than most grown men
[01:31.39]He’s a big little man with a heart so warm
[01:34.92]One little hug, and the whole room’s transformed
[01:38.46]A little charmer in a little pair of arms
[01:41.99]Full of love, sent from above
[01:45.52]Yeah, heaven knew just what it was doing
